-- Turkey Seeks Financial Aid From UN to Deal With Syrian Refugees
-- B y   S e l c a n   H a c a o g l u
-- 2012-09-14T13:28:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-14/turkey-seeks-financial-aid-from-un-to-deal-with-syrian-refugees.html
Turkey has appealed to the  United
Nations  for financial and humanitarian aid for the 80,000 Syrian
refugees now in Turkish camps, Deputy Prime Minister Besir Atalay said.  Turkey has already spent about $200 million on housing and
looking after the refugees from the civil war in neighboring
Syria, Atalay said in an interview at his office in Ankara
today. Earlier, the minister discussed the refugee situation
with Hollywood actress Angelina Jolie and UN High Commissioner
for Refugees  Antonio Guterres .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcan Hacaoglu in Ankara at 
 shacaoglu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
